{{Quote|It's a rare honor to be able to meet one's opponent face to face. You're a legend throughout the Inner Core.''"<br />"''Thank you. The honor is all mine. I'm so ''glad'' you decided to surrender.|[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Whorm Loathsom/Legends|Whorm Loathsom]] during the [[Battle of Christophsis/Legends|Battle of Christophsis]]|audio=RareHonor-TCWf.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)">[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars (film)|''Star Wars: The Clone Wars'' film]]</ref>}}
'''Arrowhead''' was an area of [[Core Worlds/Legends|the Core]] located at the tip of [[The Slice/Legends|the Slice]] and was also known as the '''Inner Core'''. Inclusive of the [[Core Worlds/Legends|Core Worlds]] between the [[Perlemian Trade Route/Legends|Perlemian Trade Route]] and the [[Corellian Run/Legends|Corellian Run]], it ranged from [[Vento system/Legends|Vento]] to [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]]. The ancient area known as the [[Tetrahedron]] was found in this area as the first inklings of modern civilization.<ref name="TEA" />

==History==
During the [[Imperial Era/Legends|Imperial Period]], [[Arrowhead Command]] was the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] fleet assigned to the defense of the Arrowhead. It was commanded by [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Blitzer Harrsk]] from the [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial''-class Star Destroyer]] [[Whirlwind (Imperial-class)|''Whirlwind'']].<ref name="Despoilers2">{{SW|url=news/the-imperial-warlords-despoilers-of-an-empire-part-2|series=The Imperial Warlords: Despoilers of an Empire|text=Part 2|nolive=1}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
''[[The Essential Atlas]]'' clearly identified the Inner Core as the Arrowhead. However, in endnotes for ''The Essential Atlas'', [[Jason Fry]] identified the Inner Core as the [[Southern Core]].

